history.content: Waitlist position for 16A will not affect your chances of getting in to the course this fall; I am manually process the wait list after reviewing each person on the waitlist.  The instructors are giving priority to EECS Freshman and graduating seniors.  If and when we have spots left for others, we will be enrolling sophomore and junior EECS before any other majors.  So in that respect, you have a leg up.  We won't know until closer to the end of Phase II how much space will be left, but you would have the option of taking EE 16A next spring.

I'm an EECS sophomore waitlisted for EE 16A during phase 1. I have looked at the enrollment numbers for the lab and discussion sections I signed up for. It seems that the one I signed up are full with long waitlists. Is it a good idea to switch to a more free lab sections since discussion sections are more flexible?
